definitions.definition: To distribute objects or pieces of something over an area, especially in a random manner.
examples: to strew sand over a floor
The files had been strewn all over the floor.

definitions.definition: To cover, or lie upon, by having been scattered.
To populate with at random points; to cause to appear randomly distributed throughout.

main_definition: ( dated , except strewn ) To distribute objects or pieces of something over an area, especially in a random manner.
secondary_definitions: ( archaic ) To cover, or lie upon, by having been scattered.
( transitive , archaic ) To spread abroad ; to disseminate .
To populate with at random points; to cause to appear randomly distributed throughout.
